### Comparison: LCA in Binary Tree vs BST
```
  Binary Tree LCA              BST LCA
  ─────────────────            ──────────────────
  Must explore both            Use value comparisons
  subtrees blindly             to navigate directly

  Time: O(N)                   Time: O(H)
  Space: O(H)                  Space: O(1) iterative

  No shortcut possible         BST property gives
                               clear direction
```

---

### Edge Cases:
```
  One node is ancestor          Both nodes are the same:
  of the other:
         6                              6
        / \                            / \
       2   8                          2   8
      / \                            / \
     0   4   p=2, q=4               0   4   p=4, q=4

  At node 2: 4 > 2 but            At node 4: 4==4
  2 == p → LCA = 2 ✓              LCA = 4 ✓
```

---

### Complexity Analysis:

**Time Complexity:** O(H), where H is the height of the BST.
- Balanced BST: O(log N)
- Skewed BST: O(N)
```
  Balanced BST             Skewed BST
       6                       1
      / \                       \
     2   8                       3
    / \ / \                       \
   0  4 7  9                       5
                                    \
  Steps ~ O(log N)                   7
                                  Steps ~ O(N)
```

**Space Complexity:** O(1), the iterative solution uses only a constant amount of extra space. No recursion stack is involved.
